The paper deals with stability of sparse convolutions, which involves topics such as signal processing, compressed sensing, and numerical analysis. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) are likely sub-categories. The paper also uses techniques from additive set theory, which suggests that cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) may be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper involves linear maps and norm bounds, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
